{
  "texts": [
    "Decision support systems powered by AI further enhance water management by integrating diverse data sources and models to inform strategies for Integrated Water Resources Management (Henriksen et al., 2022).",
    "These systems help decision-makers evaluate trade-offs between various water uses and determine the most sustainable and equitable allocation strategies.",
    "Real-time monitoring and control of water infrastructure-such as dams, canals, and treatment plants-are also enabled by AI, optimizing operations to reduce water losses and improve quality (Johnson et al., 2024).",
    "An emerging application in this realm is the use of digital twins, which combine real-time sensor data with hydrological models to enhance risk knowledge and support decision-making (Henriksen et al., 2022).",
    "These digital twins predict and monitor physical conditions on a daily basis, including wetness and drought indices, and are integral to early warning systems for extreme events (Ghaith et al., 2022)."
  ]
}